Author:  GORST
Vol / Page:  307
Edition:
Quote:  ... the service was European fashion. We sat at a table with a white cloth, forks and spoons. I felt a lingering longing for the old hospitality of former days, when the company sat on the ground, upon clean flax mats spread over the floor, when each guest had a separate portion handed to him by a Maori girl in a little green flax kit, woven for the occasion, potatoes and meat and vegetable marrow together, to which he had to help himself with his fingers.
